AWS Networking Fundamentals
This project helped me understand the core components of AWS networking, including VPCs, subnets, route tables, Internet Gateways, and Security Groups.
Infrastructure as Code
I learned how to use Terraform to automate infrastructure deployment instead of manually creating resources through the AWS Management Console. This makes deployments more consistent and repeatable.
Route Table Configuration
I gained practical experience configuring route tables and understanding how routing determines connectivity between AWS resources and the Internet.
Security Groups
This project reinforced the importance of controlling inbound and outbound traffic using Security Groups and applying the principle of least privilege.
Git and GitHub
I learned how to manage infrastructure code using Git and GitHub, including commits, repository management, .gitignore configuration, and troubleshooting common source control issues.
Documentation and Architecture Design
Creating documentation and architecture diagrams helped me better communicate the purpose and design of the environment.
